    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Activity-1: Engage government and local stakeholder to inform about Solar MUS-II project and complete required statutory requirement with government agencies at district and national level; including signing of project agreement;\r\n\r\nActivity-2: Produce Solar MUS marketing material and hold marketing events at regional and district level;\r\n\r\nActivity-3: Develop and mobilise poor friendly loan product through local and national financial institution; agree with the community on the funding mechanism to install Solar MUS system;\r\n\r\nActivity-4: Identify, establish a district level supply chain partners and organise capacity building training for supply chain partners;\r\n\r\nActivity-5: Establish economically sustainable committee institution with legal status to own and manage the system and build their capacity;\r\n\r\nActivity-6: Install 19 solar system and construct associated Multiple Water System (MUS) system in 19 sites;\r\n\r\nActivity-7: Develop and support community to implement watershed and water resource management plan;\r\n\r\nActivity-8: install metering system and develop a mechanism with the community to record and collect user fees;\r\n\r\nActivity-9: Organise capacity building training for Solar MUS beneficiaries in agriculture and micro enterprises;\r\n\r\nActivity 10- Project Monitoring and Project outcome and Impact evaluation;\r\n\r\nActivity 11- Technical Support, Capacity Building and Institutional Development for implementation of new 20x Solar MUS projects (beyond 19 x projects from Solar MUS-II);\r\n\r\nActivity 12- Installation of one unit of Hydram Pump and Control testing between hydraulic ram pumps and solar PV pumps"
      },
      "ne": null
    },
